This paper discusses a security vulnerability related to cache replacement policies in modern processors, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the potential impact on existing secure cache designs, which could fall under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper presents possible defenses against the vulnerability, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of the vulnerability in transient execution attacks, which could fall under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) or systems and control (cs.SY).
